Provide a short outline of incident-handling procedures that should be included in the policy. (again cite your arguments with scholarly and textbook references)
Looking through a lot of material on incident response Handling procedures and many examples of different incident handling procedures they all have the similar steps. One: Preparation and Prevention, Two: Detection And Analysis, Three: Containment Eradication and Recovery, and Four: Post Mortem.

Preparation and Prevention
Create a Company security policy
Go through your Infosecurity Checklist and make sure everything passes. (Items listed above)
Contact information
Set up an Incident reporting mechanism or a Operational Management System (OMS)
Perform Risk assessments regularly
User Awareness training
Network Security
Malware Prevention
Host Security
Device Management
Evidence Gathering Policy
Encryption and Cryptography
Detection And Analysis
Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)
Igoss Data Processing and Service System(IDPSs)
Antivirus, AntiSpam, and Malware Software
Third Party Monitoring Services
Operating System and Event Logs
Netflow Analyzers
Staying updated on current new vulnerabilities and exploits
Categorize severity
Network Forensics Software
Network Intrusion Detection System (NIDS) / Network Intrusion Prevention System (NIPS) / Host Intrusion Detection System HIDS / Host Intrusion Prevention System (HIPS)
Containment, Eradication, and, Recovery
Backup affected systems for later analysis
Gather appropriate evidence
Make the appropriate changes
Modifying Firewalls
Changing system setings
Changing Passwords
Etc…
Review the System
Have this plan in place in advance!
Extract and identify characteristics of adversary
Identify other affected systems
Identify what has been stolen
Identify legal ramifications
Contact Law Enforcement (LE), FBI typically interested in this sort of attack
Public Reporting
Post Mortem
Description of what happened (With all the updated information)
Date, Time, and Method of incident discovery.
Root Cause
Persons involved
Systems and Data involved
Actions taken since discovery
Immediate
Short Term
Long Term
Summary of internal discussions
Incident manager’s investigative strategy, and process
Legal issues
Timeline of investigation/recovery/ resolution
Potential Impact
Future goals
Short Term
Long Term
Immediate
Witty quote about the incident :)
“Therefore a victorious army first wins and then seeks battle; a defeated army first battles and then seeks victory.” -Sun Tzu

